    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<head>Jim to  Mon. Paul A. Rockwell <date value="1916-12-11">Dec 11th 1916</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1916-12-11">Dec 11th 1916</date></dateline>
            
            <salute>Dear old Paul:</salute>
        		</opener>
        		
            <p>
            I was very happy to 
            receive your fine letter this morning,
            old pal, and I want you to know
            how deeply I appreciate all you said.
            You know how honored I felt at
            your wanting me to be witness,
            and how much your friendship means
            to me.
            </p><p>
            I’m glad you are comfortably
            fixed up, but for some reason I
            can’t picture you in any other place
            than old 80 Rue B.  Some of
            the happiest days of my life were
            passed there.  I have done but
            little extra on the article for I’ve
            felt on the bum and then Whiskey
            chewed my fingers so its hard
            to hold a pen.  I’ll send rest 
            of it by Dudley.  Have only flown
            once since my return &mdash; this A. M.
            Nothing doing, fortunately, as my map
            case came off and I couldn’t shoot
            as I had to hold it.
            </p><p>
            I sure take off my hat to
            Chatkoff.  Queer he could arrange it
            
            <pb n="[p.2]"/>
            
            isn’t it?
            </p><p>
            Believe I’ll ask for leave to take
            baths when the rest of the boys get 
            back.  We expect Hoskier &amp; Genet soon.
            </p><p>
            Poor Marshall was made a 
            mechanic on account of his heart.
            </p><p>
            We pull out of here sometime
            next month but the place we’re 
            going isn’t any improvement.
            </p><p>
            There’s no news to send Grundy
            it al. [sic]
            </p><p>
            Give my very best regard to
            your wife.
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <salute>Yours to a cinder</salute>
            
            <signed>Jim</signed>
            
            <seg type="postscript">
            S.P. 61
            </seg>
        		</closer>
        		
